    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-13T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-13T20:00:00-05:00" n="451"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d451">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.504/2114: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Messersmith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-13T19:00:00-06:00"
                            >April 13, 1943—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>368. The Mexican Government informed the Embassy this afternoon that it has
                    agreed in principle to the contracting of 6000 non-agricultural <pb facs="0557"
                        n="543" xml:id="pg_543"/> workers in Mexico for work in the United States
                    during 1943, The Mexican Government would appreciate learning at the earliest
                    possible moment the month by month breakdown of needs during 1943 for these
                    6000, Please inform Motley of War Manpower of this message.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Messersmith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
